{"title_page": "Eben (singer)", "text_new": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Eben\n| background     = solo_singer\n| alias                 =\n| birth_name      = Emmanuel Benjamin \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1979|09|09}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]]\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n*[[gospel music|gospel]]\n*afrocentric pop}}\n| occupation     =  {{hlist|Gospel singer|Vocalist|Songwriter}}\n| years_active   = 2005\u2013present\n| label                = Hammer House of Rock\n| associated_acts  = [[Jahdiel]], Sammie Okposo, Onyeka Nwenu, Sonny Nneji, MI, Keffi\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Benjamin''' (born 9 September 1979), known professionally as '''Eben''' is a [[Nigerian]] gospel singer, vocalist, and songwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/eben-mn0002442131/biography|title=Eben|website=ALL MUSIC |access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and Education ==\nEben was born and raised in [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]], the fifth of six children. He is from a Christian family and attended Orile Primary School, and Community Grammar School, Orile, Lagos.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.concisenews.global/ebens-biography|title=Eben\u2019s Biography \u2013 Everything You Need To Know About Eben|website=Concise News|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1997, Eben started his singing career and was mentored by his elder brother as a rapper but he later discovered his talent in singing and became a gospel singer. In 2005, as a gospel singer, Eben became popular after his first big public appearance, at a youth conference organized by Pastor Chris where \"Imarama\" was first heard.\n\nIn 2006, Eben was a member of Christ Embassy founded by Pastor Chris Oyakhilome. In 2007, Eben released his first album, \"On the Rock\", which includes songs like \u201cImaranma\u201d, \u201dGod Dey\u201d, \u201dIwo Nikan\u201d, \"I Don Hammer\", and other tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2019/09/28/i-grew-up-around-music-its-a-gift-from-above/|title=I Grew Up Around Music, It\u2019s a Gift from Above|website=Thisdaylive|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2019/04/27/eben-gospel-is-my-lifestyle-thats-what-sets-me-apart/|title=EBEN: Gospel is My Lifestyle, that\u2019s what Sets Me Apart|website=This Day|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\nIn 2010, he released a follow-up album, \u201cPhenomenon\u201d, which included songs like \"Supper Man\", \"Imele Papa\", \"Siya Nma\" and several other tracks.\nIn 2013, Eben released another album titled \u201cJustified\u201d, which included songs like \u201cYou Alone Are Worthy\u201d, \"Onye Nwem\", \"How I Love You\", \"For Ever\" and \"All The Way\".\nEben also has a record label called Hammer House of Rock, with a business arm called the Hammer House Ventures, which specializes in video and music production, event management and interior decoration. And also another album titled \"Magnified\", with songs like \u201cStayed On You\u201d, \"Everything\", \"Idi Nma\", \"Lifted Hands\" and other worship songs.\nEben went viral after he released a song titled \u201cVictory\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/itll-be-strange-if-my-children-dont-become-singers-eben/|title=It\u2019ll be strange if my children don\u2019t become singers \u2013 Eben|website=PUNCH|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 September 2019, Eben host a life concert called Joyful Noise 2019 which featured top gospel musicians and also popular American musicians Bob Fitts and [[Phil Thompson]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/bob-fitts-phil-thompson-storm-nigeria-for-eben/|title=Bob Fitts, Phil Thompson storm Nigeria for Eben|website=The Nation|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.guardian.ng/life/bob-fitts-phil-thompson-others-for-ebens-joyful-noice/|title=Bob Fitts, Phil Thompson, Others For Eben\u2019s Joyful Noice|website=The Guardian|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Studio Albums ===\n* On the Rock (2007)\n* Phenomenon (2010)\n* Justified (2013)\n* Magnified<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gospelhotspot.net/tag/eben-songs/|title=Tag: Eben Songs|website=Gospelhotspot|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jesusful.com/category/nigerian-gospel-music-songs/artiste/eben-songs/|title=Eben Songs|website=Jesusful|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* In 2012, he won the PBO Musical Video Awards\n* \u2018Best Male Artiste\u2019 Africa gospel Music Awards UK\n* Best Male Artiste at the National Gospel Awards Nigeria\n* Best Gospel Video Award at the Nigerian Music Awards\n* Best Gospel Video \u2018NMVA\u2019\n* In the year 2013, he won the Best West Africa award at the Africa Gospel Music Awards\n* in 2014, he won the Album of the Year at the Crystal Awards\n* Best Songwriter of the Year at the Lima awards\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn 30 November 2013, Eben married [[Jahdiel]] (Grace Okoduwa), his fellow gospel singer, with whom he has two children. In December 2013, Eben and [[Jahdiel]] had a white wedding and was joined in holy matrimony by Pastor Chris Oyakhilome of Christ Embassy.\n\n== References ==\n[https://dailygospelvibe.com/tag/eben-songs-download/]{{Reflist}}\n\n<br />\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Nigerian gospel singers]]\n[[Category:People from Lagos State by occupation]]\n[[Category:Nigerian performers of Christian music]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Eben\n| background     = solo_singer\n| alias                 =\n| birth_name      = Emmanuel Benjamin \n| birth_date       = {{Birth date and age|mf=yes|1979|09|09}}\n| birth_place      = [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]]\n| genre               = {{flatlist|\n*[[gospel music|gospel]]\n*afrocentric pop}}\n| occupation     =  {{hlist|Gospel singer|Vocalist|Songwriter}}\n| years_active   = 2005\u2013present\n| label                = Hammer House of Rock\n| associated_acts  = [[Jahdiel]], Sammie Okposo, Onyeka Nwenu, Sonny Nneji, MI, Keffi\n}}\n\n'''Emmanuel Benjamin''' (born 9 September 1979), known professionally as '''Eben''' is a [[Nigerian]] gospel singer, vocalist, and songwriter.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/eben-mn0002442131/biography|title=Eben|website=ALL MUSIC |access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Early life and Education ==\nEben was born and raised in [[Lagos]], [[Nigeria]], the fifth of six children. He is from a Christian family and attended Orile Primary School, and Community Grammar School, Orile, Lagos.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.concisenews.global/ebens-biography|title=Eben\u2019s Biography \u2013 Everything You Need To Know About Eben|website=Concise News|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Career ==\nIn 1997, Eben started his singing career and was mentored by his elder brother as a rapper but he later discovered his talent in singing and became a gospel singer. In 2005, as a gospel singer, Eben became popular after his first big public appearance, at a youth conference organized by Pastor Chris where \"Imarama\" was first heard.\n\nIn 2006, Eben was a member of Christ Embassy founded by Pastor Chris Oyakhilome. In 2007, Eben released his first album, \"On the Rock\", which includes songs like \u201cImaranma\u201d, \u201dGod Dey\u201d, \u201dIwo Nikan\u201d, \"I Don Hammer\", and other tracks.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2019/09/28/i-grew-up-around-music-its-a-gift-from-above/|title=I Grew Up Around Music, It\u2019s a Gift from Above|website=Thisdaylive|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thisdaylive.com/index.php/2019/04/27/eben-gospel-is-my-lifestyle-thats-what-sets-me-apart/|title=EBEN: Gospel is My Lifestyle, that\u2019s what Sets Me Apart|website=This Day|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\nIn 2010, he released a follow-up album, \u201cPhenomenon\u201d, which included songs like \"Supper Man\", \"Imele Papa\", \"Siya Nma\" and several other tracks.\nIn 2013, Eben released another album titled \u201cJustified\u201d, which included songs like \u201cYou Alone Are Worthy\u201d, \"Onye Nwem\", \"How I Love You\", \"For Ever\" and \"All The Way\".\nEben also has a record label called Hammer House of Rock, with a business arm called the Hammer House Ventures, which specializes in video and music production, event management and interior decoration. And also another album titled \"Magnified\", with songs like \u201cStayed On You\u201d, \"Everything\", \"Idi Nma\", \"Lifted Hands\" and other worship songs.\nEben went viral after he released a song titled \u201cVictory\u201d.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punchng.com/itll-be-strange-if-my-children-dont-become-singers-eben/|title=It\u2019ll be strange if my children don\u2019t become singers \u2013 Eben|website=PUNCH|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nOn 15 September 2019, Eben host a life concert called Joyful Noise 2019 which featured top gospel musicians and also popular American musicians Bob Fitts and [[Phil Thompson]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thenationonlineng.net/bob-fitts-phil-thompson-storm-nigeria-for-eben/|title=Bob Fitts, Phil Thompson storm Nigeria for Eben|website=The Nation|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://m.guardian.ng/life/bob-fitts-phil-thompson-others-for-ebens-joyful-noice/|title=Bob Fitts, Phil Thompson, Others For Eben\u2019s Joyful Noice|website=The Guardian|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Discography ==\n=== Studio Albums ===\n* On the Rock (2007)\n* Phenomenon (2010)\n* Justified (2013)\n* Magnified<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gospelhotspot.net/tag/eben-songs/|title=Tag: Eben Songs|website=Gospelhotspot|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://jesusful.com/category/nigerian-gospel-music-songs/artiste/eben-songs/|title=Eben Songs|website=Jesusful|access-date=20 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n* In 2012, he won the PBO Musical Video Awards\n* \u2018Best Male Artiste\u2019 Africa gospel Music Awards UK\n* Best Male Artiste at the National Gospel Awards Nigeria\n* Best Gospel Video Award at the Nigerian Music Awards\n* Best Gospel Video \u2018NMVA\u2019\n* In the year 2013, he won the Best West Africa award at the Africa Gospel Music Awards\n* in 2014, he won the Album of the Year at the Crystal Awards\n* Best Songwriter of the Year at the Lima awards\n\n== Personal life ==\nOn 30 November 2013, Eben married [[Jahdiel]] (Grace Okoduwa), his fellow gospel singer, with whom he has two children. In December 2013, Eben and [[Jahdiel]] had a white wedding and was joined in holy matrimony by Pastor Chris Oyakhilome of Christ Embassy.\n\n== References ==\n[https://dailygospelvibe.com/tag/eben-songs-download/]{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Nigerian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[Category:Nigerian gospel singers]]\n[[Category:People from Lagos State by occupation]]\n[[Category:Nigerian performers of Christian music]]\n[[Category:1979 births]]\n<br />\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eben_(singer)"}
